ls -> check the contents 
pwd -> u will find that u are in home directory  
       /home/cloudera
cat > /home/cloudera/Processfile1.txt
hdfs dfs -ls /   -> find the number of items 
hdfs dfs -mkdir /inputfolder1  -> create a directory inputfolder1
hdfs dfs -put /home/cloudera/Processfile1.txt /inputfolder1/   -> put the contents of Processfile1.txt into inputfolder1
hdfs dfs -cat /inputfolder/Processfile1.txt  -> displays the contents in the Processfile1.txt
hadoop jar /home/cloudera/Wordcount.jar Wordcount /inputfolder1/Processfile1.txt /out1  -> it will perform the map and reduce operation
hdfs dfs -ls /out1  -> out1 is the output folder. Now, display the contents in the cout1 folder.

Finally display the output will be the number of words followed by the occurences.
